snippet.title: 755. FUNNY RUSSIAN CITIZENSHIP TEST with Amber & Paul
snippet.description:
Can Luke, Amber & Paul pass this funny Russian citizenship test which was written and sent in by a Russian LEPster? Join us as we attempt to answer questions which (apparently) every Russian person would know. This could be embarrassing! 
P.S. I am 99% sure that this really is the final episode of 2021.
Episode page (download the audio & read the full citizenship test from Vadim) https://wp.me/p4IuUx-pPY
LEP Premium (vocabulary, grammar & pronunciation lessons) https://www.teacherluke.co.uk/premiuminfo
LEP T-shirts & merch https://www.teacherluke.co.uk/merch
Episode contents
00:00 Welcome / chatting to Paul
07:45 Introduction to the Russian Citizenship Test (sent by Vadim)
15:29 Example question - What happens on 3rd September?
21:41 Question 1 - A famous Russian cartoon about two animals that fight
22:31 Amber arrives
32:15 Question 2 - What animal does every Russian see on the streets every day?
36:51 Question 3 - 3rd September (again) Amber tries to answer 
38:31 Question 4 - What do Russians expect lobsters to do on top of a mountain?
42:22 Question 5 - What French name is often mentioned on New Year's Eve?
47:31 Question 6 - What tree do Russians want to hug when they're sad?
52:47 Question 7 - What is the correct way to drink vodka in Russia?
01:02:58 Results
